{
  "final_answer": "# Netflix's Average Revenue Per Paying User (ARPU) Change from 2019 to 2024\n\n## Summary\n\nNetflix's global average monthly revenue per paying membership increased from **$10.82 in 2019** to **$11.70 in 2024**, representing an **absolute increase of $0.88 per month** (or **~8.13% growth**). On an annualized basis, this equates to an increase from **$129.84 per year** to **$140.40 per year**.\n\n---\n\n## Global (Worldwide) Average Monthly Revenue Per Paying Membership\n\n| Year | Monthly ARPU | Annualized ARPU (×12) |\n|:----:|:-----------:|:--------------------:|\n| 2019 | $10.82 | $129.84 |\n| 2020 | $10.91 | $130.92 |\n| 2021 | $11.67 | $140.04 |\n| 2022 | $11.76 | $141.12 |\n| 2023 | $11.64 | $139.68 |\n| 2024 | **$11.70** | **$140.40** |\n\n**Change (2019 → 2024):**\n- **Absolute change (monthly):** $11.70 − $10.82 = **+$0.88/month**\n- **Absolute change (annualized):** $140.40 − $129.84 = **+$10.56/year**\n- **Percentage change:** ($11.70 − $10.82) ÷ $10.82 × 100 = **+8.13%**\n\n---\n\n## Regional Breakdown\n\nThe data below shows the average monthly revenue per paying membership by region from 2019 to 2024.\n\n### UCAN (United States & Canada)\n\n| Year | Monthly ARPU | Change vs. Prior Year |\n|:----:|:-----------:|:--------------------:|\n| 2019 | $12.57 | — |\n| 2020 | $13.32 | +6.0% |\n| 2021 | $14.56 | +9.3% |\n| 2022 | $15.86 | +8.9% |\n| 2023 | $16.28 | +2.6% |\n| 2024 | **$17.20** | +5.7% |\n\n**Change 2019 → 2024:** +$4.63/month (+36.83%)\n\n### EMEA (Europe, Middle East & Africa)\n\n| Year | Monthly ARPU | Change vs. Prior Year |\n|:----:|:-----------:|:--------------------:|\n| 2019 | $10.33 | — |\n| 2020 | $10.72 | +3.8% |\n| 2021 | $11.63 | +8.5% |\n| 2022 | $10.99 | −5.5% |\n| 2023 | $10.87 | −1.1% |\n| 2024 | **$10.96** | +0.8% |\n\n**Change 2019 → 2024:** +$0.63/month (+6.10%)\n\n### LATAM (Latin America)\n\n| Year | Monthly ARPU | Change vs. Prior Year |\n|:----:|:-----------:|:--------------------:|\n| 2019 | $8.21 | — |\n| 2020 | $7.45 | −9.3% |\n| 2021 | $7.73 | +3.8% |\n| 2022 | $8.48 | +9.7% |\n| 2023 | $8.66 | +2.1% |\n| 2024 | **$8.24** | −4.9% |\n\n**Change 2019 → 2024:** +$0.03/month (+0.37%)\n\n### APAC (Asia-Pacific)\n\n| Year | Monthly ARPU | Change vs. Prior Year |\n|:----:|:-----------:|:--------------------:|\n| 2019 | $9.24 | — |\n| 2020 | $9.12 | −1.3% |\n| 2021 | $9.56 | +4.8% |\n| 2022 | $8.50 | −11.1% |\n| 2023 | $7.64 | −10.1% |\n| 2024 | **$7.29** | −4.6% |\n\n**Change 2019 → 2024:** −$1.95/month (−21.10%)\n\n---\n\n## Key Observations\n\n1. **Global ARPU grew modestly** (+8.13%) over the six-year period, with fluctuations along the way — peaking at $11.76 in 2022 before dipping slightly in 2023 and recovering in 2024.\n\n2. **Regional divergence:** The UCAN region showed the strongest ARPU growth (+36.83%), driven by price increases and plan mix changes. In contrast, APAC ARPU declined significantly (−21.10%), primarily due to the growing subscriber base in lower-ARPU markets and foreign exchange headwinds.\n\n3. **2024 UCAN ARPU:** Note that the official SEC filing reports **$17.20** (not $17.26 as cited in some third-party sources). The SEC 10-K data is used as the authoritative source throughout this analysis.\n\n4. **Currency effects:** Netflix's reported ARPU is impacted by foreign exchange rate fluctuations. On a constant currency basis, the company noted a 4% increase in global ARPU in 2024, with even larger constant-currency growth in LATAM (+21%) despite the reported USD ARPU decline.\n\n---\n\n## Sources\n\n```json\n{\n    \"sources\": [\n        {\n            \"url\": \"https://www.sec.gov/Archives/edgar/data/1065280/000106528020000040/form10kq419.htm\",\n            \"name\": \"Netflix 10-K for Fiscal Year Ended December 31, 2019\"\n        },\n        {\n            \"url\": \"https://www.sec.gov/Archives/edgar/data/1065280/000106528021000040/nflx-20201231.htm\",\n            \"name\": \"Netflix 10-K for Fiscal Year Ended December 31, 2020\"\n        },\n        {\n            \"url\": \"https://www.sec.gov/Archives/edgar/data/1065280/000106528022000036/nflx-20211231.htm\",\n            \"name\": \"Netflix 10-K for Fiscal Year Ended December 31, 2021\"\n        },\n        {\n            \"url\": \"https://www.sec.gov/Archives/edgar/data/1065280/000106528023000035/nflx-20221231.htm\",\n            \"name\": \"Netflix 10-K for Fiscal Year Ended December 31, 2022\"\n        },\n        {\n            \"url\": \"https://www.sec.gov/Archives/edgar/data/1065280/000106528024000030/nflx-20231231.htm\",\n            \"name\": \"Netflix 10-K for Fiscal Year Ended December 31, 2023\"\n        },\n        {\n            \"url\": \"https://www.sec.gov/Archives/edgar/data/1065280/000106528025000044/nflx-20241231.htm\",\n            \"name\": \"Netflix 10-K for Fiscal Year Ended December 31, 2024\"\n        }\n    ]\n}\n```",
